result.execSummary:
The defendant Seth J. Holland was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).
  • Failure to Support Child (120 Days+), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.22(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency. 
**EXTRADITION COSTS OF $1519.00 ARE TO BE PAID THROUGH THE WISCONSIN SUPPORT COLLECTIONS TRUST FUND (WISCTF) NOT THROUGH THE DEPARTMENT OF CORRECTIONS OR THE WAUSHARA COUNTY CLERK OF COURT**
Defendant to obtain and maintain full time employment, unless medically excused by a treating physician.

Defendant to maintain timely, uninterrupted payments as ordered in Waushara Co Case No. 06PA22.  Orders subject to modification in the future by further order of the Court. All payments are to be paid through the Wisconsin Support Collections Trust Fund (WISCTF), not through the Department of Corrections. Child Support obligation under this order is to commence November 1, 2014. Defendant is to confer directly with the Child Support Agency for a total amount to be paid each month.
Defendant is to provide to the Waushara County Child Support Agency, in writing, any change of address within 48 hours.

timeConds.notes: With Huber-No Good Time Credit. Court directs jail sentence to be served as follows: The first 6 months to be served forthwith, with 90 days credit. Balance of 6 month sentence STAYED-If defendant misses a CSUP payment he is to serve the balance of the jail sentence directly. For the first missed payment within the 5 year probation period the defendant will serve 2 months. The second missed payment within the 5 year probation period the defendant will serve the remaining 4 months.

records.addlTxt: 10CF-58, 12CF-80 and 14CF-53 - All Cases Called @ 1:30 PM: Defendant Seth J. Holland in court, in custody, with attorney Bryan D Keberlein.  Scott C Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Global resolution recited by DA.  Def and counsel confirm resolution.  Court entertains waiver of pre-lim hearings as to 12CF-80 and 14CF-53.  Court accepts knowing and voluntary waiver of pre-lim hearings.  Def BOT.  Terms of bifurcated SEH explained.  INFO Filed as to each case.  Receipt Admitted - Reading waived.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. 12CF-80 Plea Ct 1:  NC  14CF-53 Plea Cts 1 and 2:  NC Court accepts pleas and enters JOC.  Cts 3 and 4 of 12CF-80 DRI.  10CF-58 also DRI.  Argument by DA.  Argument by SPD.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  As to each of the 3 counts:  S/W -5 yrs probation - concurrent terms.  Conditions:  1 yr WCJ as a cond'l sentence with Huber and no GT, 90 days TS credit - segregated into 3 different parts.  1st part of conditional sentence of 6 mos to be served directly with 3 more months to serve forthwith with a release give or take of 9/15/14 - the remaining 6 mos stayed - those periods are to be served directly if Def misses any CSUP payments as directed under 06PA-22.  The second portion of sentence of 60 days to be served if any missed payments for the first time during the 5 yr period of probation.  3rd segment for a period of 4 mos to be imposed and served if any payments are missed for the 2nd time of the 5 yr period of supervision.   1st missed payment 2 mos - 2nd time it happens 4 mos to serve.  Period of jail time applicable only to Ct 1 of 14CF-53.  As to all counts conditions of probation:  Maintain payments as ordered as per 06PA-22 subject to further order of the Court; maintain full time employment; provide CSA with any change of address in writing within 48 hours; Court Costs including DNA surcharge as to each count and including $1519 extradition fees.  CSUP obligation under this order to commence 11/1/14.  Def to confer directly with CSA as to total amount to be paid each month.  Court will not address today as all parties are not present.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 13, 2014 at 01:30 pm.
Ex Parte Letter to Cynthia Ratliff
Status conference on June 10, 2014 at 09:30 am.
